Package: climr
Title: Quantifying sources of uncertainty in projections of future climate 
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2019-10-23
Authors@R: c(
    person(c("Paul", "J."), "Northrop", email = "p.northrop@ucl.ac.uk",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Yue", "Zhang", role = c("aut", "cph")))
Description: This could lead to a great understanding of past, present and
  future climate change and variability in a multi-model framework.By 
  analysing the CMIP5 and CMIP6 climate data, we uses the two-way random-effected ANOVA
  model for analysing the variability of climate and finding the main source 
  of climate uncertainty, following the structure of Northrop and Chandler (2014)
  <DOI: 10.1175/JCLI-D-14-00265.1>. We are mainly using the restricted maximum likelihood (REML) estimation
  and the Bayesian inference with the Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) techniques.
Imports: graphics,
